  "body": "For example this method : \n\n```java\nprivate Wei priceOf(final Transaction transaction, final Optional<Long> baseFee) {\n   final TransactionPriceCalculator transactionPriceCalculator =\n       transaction.getType().equals(TransactionType.EIP1559)\n           ? EIP1559_CALCULATOR\n           : FRONTIER_CALCULATOR;\n   return transactionPriceCalculator.price(transaction, baseFee);\n } \n```\nThe 'EIP1559_CALCULATOR' manage non EIP1559 transaction so this check is useless. But in order to have something that work before London we need to have different **TransactionReplacementByPriceRule** behavior for PRE and POST London\n\nMaybe getting the valid TransactionPriceCalculator thanks to the protocolSpec in order to not have **if else** condition **\n    protocolSchedule.getByBlockNumber().getTransactionPriceCalculator()**\n",
